<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="598" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.516/72.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At the request of Bank, Legation protested on the 9th instant by note to
                            the Haitian Government against the issue of Treasury notes and also
                            against the taking of the Treasury service from the Bank as violating
                            contract of Bank and therefore injurious to American interests therein.
                            French Minister has also filed protest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>